    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** as our premier offensive anchor, boasting a dominant 79.79 efficiency score. The matchup against Smith, S is ideal, but the true driver here is the combination of his elevated lineup spot and a rare strategic advantage regarding stolen bases: the opposing pitcher\u2019s slow delivery suggests high upside for **Gunnar Henderson** on the basepaths. Alongside him, **Josh Lowe** (71.68) and **Kyle Tucker** (67.98) provide excellent coverage. **Josh Lowe** benefits significantly from a soft matchup against L\u00f3pez, R, where his dynamic platoon advantage and a favorable park factor allow him to clear our \"Strong\" threshold despite hitting in the lower third of the order. \n\nOur most challenging decision centered on the utility and bench spots, where **Miguel Vargas** (50.02) ultimately fell just short of a start. While his recent profile is stable, he lacked the explosive platoon or park factors that propelled **Nolan Schanuel** (62.47) into the lineup; **Nolan Schanuel** enjoys the same favorable conditions against L\u00f3pez, R as **Josh Lowe**, making him a higher-floor play for our Roto constraints. We remain cautious regarding **Jackson Merrill**, whose 51.93 score is tempered by a difficult assignment against Skenes. The SP skill gap here is steep, and despite **Jackson Merrill**\u2019s dynamic platoon advantage, the threat of an elite catcher nullifying his speed upside makes him a marginal play. We are also continuing to monitor **Jordan Westburg**, who remains sidelined on the IL, as we look to stabilize our middle infield depth.",
